The probability that three random chords in a circle intersect pairwise, forming a triangular piece, is calculated by considering the cyclic order of the six endpoints. There are \(8\) favorable cyclic orders out of \(120\) possible, giving a probability of \(\frac{1}{15}\). Thus, \(m = 1\), \(n = 15\), and \(\gcd(m, n) = 1\), so \(k = \gcd(m, n) + 1 = 2\).

The equation becomes \((x^2 + 2x + 3)^{(x^2 + 2x + 3)^{(x^2 + 2x + 3)}} = 2012\). Let \(t = x^2 + 2x + 3 \geq 2\). The function \(f(t) = t^{t^t}\) is strictly increasing for \(t \geq 2\), so there is a unique \(t_0 > 2\) satisfying \(t_0^{t_0^{t_0}} = 2012\). The quadratic \(x^2 + 2x + 3 = t_0\) yields two real solutions whose sum is \(-2\), regardless of \(t_0\). Therefore, the sum of all real solutions is \(-2\).

